<i>Love wave over you </i>

99
00:04:57,163 --> 00:05:00,300
Us, Journey, Coffee. That's a wrap!

100
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:04,070
- Thank you.
- Thanks, guys.

101
00:05:06,839 --> 00:05:09,275
Our last Polaroid photo.

102
00:05:11,277 --> 00:05:12,612
We really did it.

103
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,615
Nice.

104
00:05:15,682 --> 00:05:18,084
Look, it turned into a heart.

105
00:05:19,752 --> 00:05:22,622
It's so good!
This is such a memorable scene.

106
00:05:22,689 --> 00:05:25,124
These are gonna be friendships for life.

107
00:05:26,192 --> 00:05:28,561
- Can I get a little help?
- Yeah, with what?

108
00:05:28,628 --> 00:05:32,031
Could you maybe go rinse these over there?

109
00:05:32,532 --> 00:05:34,500
- Maybe! Yes.
- Yeah, let's do that.

110
00:05:34,567 --> 00:05:37,170
Don't you put black pepper in the patties?

111
00:05:37,670 --> 00:05:40,740
- Nothing to do, so I came over.
- Okay, thanks.

112
00:05:41,507 --> 00:05:44,377
Do you think he really likes me?

113
00:05:44,944 --> 00:05:46,612
- Huh?
- Does he?

114
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:50,249
Oh, you two are still on that stage?
You're not feeling secure yet?

115
00:05:50,316 --> 00:05:51,784
I'm not. Not at all.

116
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:53,519
That's a pretty big deal, you know.

117
00:05:53,586 --> 00:05:55,088
Seriously, yeah.

118
00:05:55,888 --> 00:06:00,259
It still feels like I like him more than
he likes me. You know what I mean?

119
00:06:00,326 --> 00:06:04,664
If I really liked someone,
I'd want to talk to them all the time.

120
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,132
Like, if I liked you, Hiroya,

121
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:08,568
you'd be the first person
I'd wanna say good morning to.

122
00:06:08,634 --> 00:06:10,970
- Fair.
- But he's not like that in the mornings.

123
00:06:11,471 --> 00:06:14,140
When I don't go up to him,
he keeps his distance.

124
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:15,742
It was the same thing this morning.

125
00:06:17,410 --> 00:06:18,344
Morning.

126
00:06:18,811 --> 00:06:19,779
You're late though.

127
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:21,180
I overslept so bad.

128
00:06:21,247 --> 00:06:23,783
<i>Ah, so he didn't say</i>
<i>good morning back there.</i>

129
00:06:23,850 --> 00:06:25,785
<i>So he wanted a hug or something?</i>

130
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:28,254
He doesn't chase after you, then?

131
00:06:28,321 --> 00:06:30,523
Exactly. I'm always the one going to him.

132
00:06:31,023 --> 00:06:34,560
That's why I end up thinking,
"Wait, does he really like me?"

133
00:06:35,595 --> 00:06:40,366
The souvenir itself isn't a big deal,
but it's the thought behind it.

134
00:06:40,433 --> 00:06:44,337
"I thought of everyone and bought this."
"I thought of Ryuki and bought this."

135
00:06:44,404 --> 00:06:46,139
That's fine. I get that part.

136
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:47,540
- Yeah.
- Mmm.

137
00:06:48,274 --> 00:06:50,009
But there's nothing just for me.

138
00:06:51,010 --> 00:06:53,413
The more I think about it,
the sadder I get.

139
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:57,350
And I start wondering,
"Do you actually like me?"

140
00:06:59,685 --> 00:07:02,822
You know, I actually think
I'm similar to Huwei in that way.

141
00:07:02,889 --> 00:07:07,794
When we're in a group, I'm really not good
at being clingy to just one person.

142
00:07:08,294 --> 00:07:09,629
Oh, that's what it is?

143
00:07:09,695 --> 00:07:12,031
Or maybe he's just playing it cool
to hide his blushing.

144
00:07:12,098 --> 00:07:14,200
It definitely doesn't mean
he doesn't like you.

145
00:07:15,368 --> 00:07:18,938
I know he likes me,
but I can't help second-guessing it.

146
00:07:19,005 --> 00:07:20,640
- Right.
- "Do you really like me?"

147
00:07:20,706 --> 00:07:23,209
You two had a lot of chances
to go off alone, right?

148
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,143
Mmm.

149
00:07:24,210 --> 00:07:29,449
I feel like he's been trying
to change things since then.

150
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,084
- I really felt that.
- Mmm.

151
00:07:32,151 --> 00:07:34,153
Like he's really trying
to take you seriously.

152
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:36,155
That's how it looked from the outside.

153
00:07:36,222 --> 00:07:38,024
He has no idea, though.

154
00:07:38,724 --> 00:07:41,994
Seriously,
tell him sooner rather than later.

155
00:07:42,061 --> 00:07:43,529
If you don't, he won't get it.

156
00:07:43,596 --> 00:07:46,632
That's right.
Just drop the pride aside for a second.

157
00:07:47,266 --> 00:07:49,502
Yeah. He really won't understand
unless you tell him.

158
00:07:49,569 --> 00:07:52,605
- You're right. Maybe he doesn't realize.
- I don't think he does.

159
00:07:52,672 --> 00:07:55,274
That's your fate
for falling for a guy like him.

160
00:07:55,341 --> 00:07:57,376
- My fate?
- It is.

161
00:07:57,443 --> 00:07:58,478
It's your fate.

162
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:02,548
- And it'll definitely keep happening.
- Yeah…

163
00:08:02,615 --> 00:08:04,417
Even if you two end up together.

164
00:08:04,917 --> 00:08:07,854
- <i>They're so kind.</i>
- <i>Such good advice!</i>

165
00:08:10,356 --> 00:08:12,225
Should we start grilling?

166
00:08:12,725 --> 00:08:15,127
- Let's start with the meat.
- Meat!

167
00:08:15,628 --> 00:08:17,330
- Get cookin'!
- Grill it!

168
00:08:17,396 --> 00:08:18,431
Grill it, grill it!

169
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:21,534
- Let's start with four pieces.
- Can I just put them all on?

170
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,669
- That looks so good.
- Grilling Bomi.

171
00:08:25,137 --> 00:08:27,473
This meat is definitely going to be tasty.

172
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,943
- I'm digging in.
- This is insanely good.

173
00:08:31,911 --> 00:08:33,246
Mmm, mmm!

174
00:08:33,813 --> 00:08:35,381
- Stupid good.
- Is it good?

175
00:08:35,448 --> 00:08:36,516
- Yeah.
- So good.

176
00:08:36,582 --> 00:08:38,351
- Right? It's so good.
- So good.

177
00:08:39,785 --> 00:08:45,458
Some of you have been living together
for almost two months now, right?

178
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:48,928
Any moments or places
that really stuck with you?

179
00:08:48,995 --> 00:08:53,432
For me, the coffee time with Hiroya.
In the morning and…

180
00:08:53,499 --> 00:08:54,600
We did that a few times.

181
00:08:54,667 --> 00:09:00,473
I could talk with him about the stuff
I was struggling with and ask for advice.

182
00:09:01,741 --> 00:09:05,645
<i>Because of that, I feel like</i>
<i>it brought me closer to Hiroya.</i>

183
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:10,249
For me, that time was meaningful for me.

184
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:13,419
For me, yoga with Huwei.

185
00:09:14,487 --> 00:09:15,688
Oh yeah, you were doing yoga.

186
00:09:15,755 --> 00:09:18,491
You were the first person
who ever did yoga with me.

187
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:22,595
<i>Yeah. It was really fun.</i>
<i>It's a big memory for me.</i>

188
00:09:23,863 --> 00:09:25,164
<i>What about you, Jobu?</i>

189
00:09:25,231 --> 00:09:26,832
The hallway on the second floor.

190
00:09:26,899 --> 00:09:30,636
Everyone would hang around downstairs
until about eleven,

191
00:09:30,703 --> 00:09:32,605
then we'd all head upstairs.

192
00:09:32,672 --> 00:09:35,741
And before we said goodnight,
there'd always be this little moment.

193
00:09:35,808 --> 00:09:37,443
Some people stayed for a bit, some didn't,

194
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:40,046
but that hallway became our spot
for those last small talks.

195
00:09:40,112 --> 00:09:43,783
<i>Personally, I really like that spot.</i>
<i>A lot has happened there, you know?</i>

196
00:09:43,849 --> 00:09:45,651
And that made me really happy.

197
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:51,924
Anyone has anything
you want to do in Sapporo?

198
00:09:52,491 --> 00:09:54,961
Well, since
we're going somewhere different,

199
00:09:55,461 --> 00:09:59,298
I'd like us to have conversations
we haven't had before.

200
00:09:59,365 --> 00:10:00,199
Mmm.

201
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:04,737
I want to talk about deeper stuff as well.
I want time to really face each other.

202
00:10:04,804 --> 00:10:06,839
I want us to make the most of the time.

203
00:10:06,906 --> 00:10:07,773
Yeah.

204
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,108
Let's enjoy tomorrow!

205
00:10:09,175 --> 00:10:10,910
- Let's not fight.
- Got it.

206
00:10:10,977 --> 00:10:12,979
Yay!

207
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,630
<i>Honestly,</i>
<i>I wanted to talk about a lot of things.</i>

208
00:10:30,696 --> 00:10:36,535
Since I realized we didn't really get to
do that, I felt a bit unsettled about it.

209
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:38,237
Yeah.

210
00:10:38,938 --> 00:10:42,008
<i>I end up joking around</i>
<i>whenever things get serious.</i>

211
00:10:42,074 --> 00:10:43,943
I get embarrassed,
and I can't say what I want,

212
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:46,145
and I never know
what kind of face I'm supposed to make,

213
00:10:46,212 --> 00:10:48,848
<i>so I end up turning it into a joke.</i>

214
00:10:48,914 --> 00:10:52,184
<i>Maybe a part of me just doesn't</i>
<i>want to show my weak side.</i>

215
00:10:53,452 --> 00:10:55,621
I'm really aware of that in myself.

216
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:58,190
Next time, I want to push myself

217
00:10:58,691 --> 00:11:01,260
to flip that switch
and talk a little more seriously.

218
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:15,508
<i>- "Think easy," she said</i>
<i>- She said</i>

219
00:11:16,042 --> 00:11:18,244
<i>"Forever young and so wild"</i>

220
00:11:18,310 --> 00:11:21,313
<i>"Or pull a gun and then fire it"</i>

221
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:24,717
<i>- "Easy," she said</i>
<i>- She said</i>

222
00:11:25,651 --> 00:11:30,723
<i>"You're never young if you don't run</i>
<i>So get over"</i>

223
00:11:30,790 --> 00:11:33,959
<i>- We still got walls on both sides</i>
<i>- Sides</i>

224
00:11:34,026 --> 00:11:35,561
<i>Maybe</i>

225
00:11:35,628 --> 00:11:38,397
<i>- I wanna know how to climb</i>
<i>- Climb</i>

226
00:11:38,464 --> 00:11:39,832
<i>We're blind, blind</i>

227
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:42,268
<i>- Blind</i>
<i>- How'd we get air all this time?</i>

228
00:11:42,334 --> 00:11:44,370
<i>- This time</i>
<i>- These things</i>

229
00:11:44,437 --> 00:11:46,939
<i>- These things</i>
<i>- I never thought when you were mine</i>

230
00:11:47,006 --> 00:11:49,742
<i>We used to break it together</i>

231
00:11:49,809 --> 00:11:51,711
<i>Oh, oh, oh</i>

232
00:11:51,777 --> 00:11:55,881
<i>We used to dive</i>
<i>In our highest feelings</i>

233
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,884
<i>Are we growing older together?</i>

234
00:11:58,951 --> 00:12:00,853
<i>Oh, oh, oh</i>

235
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:05,558
<i>I don't wanna miss anything</i>
<i>When I'm dreaming about</i>

236
00:12:05,624 --> 00:12:08,828
<i>When we were dazed and confused</i>

237
00:12:13,833 --> 00:12:15,768
What great weather!

238
00:12:15,835 --> 00:12:18,771
- Beautiful day today.
- Literally not a single cloud.

239
00:12:18,838 --> 00:12:20,239
The weather is amazing.

240
00:12:24,009 --> 00:12:25,511
Oh, I'm sitting on this side?

241
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:27,246
- You don't like it?
- I don't mind.

242
00:12:27,313 --> 00:12:28,748
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

243
00:12:31,717 --> 00:12:35,521
<i>I knew my days</i>

244
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:42,261
<i>Darlin', I signed out</i>
<i>And I'm thinkin' about you in the summer</i>

245
00:12:42,328 --> 00:12:43,963
Anyone want milk tea?

246
00:12:44,029 --> 00:12:45,397
- I do!
- I'll take a banana.

247
00:12:45,464 --> 00:12:47,633
- Banana?
- How many bananas do we have?

248
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,001
- Four.
- Can I get one?

249
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:52,838
We have bananas, strawberries,
chocolate, cookies and milk tea.

250
00:12:52,905 --> 00:12:54,406
- Hey, Mommy?
- Yes, dear?

251
00:12:54,473 --> 00:12:55,775
- Do you have a trash bag?
- Huh?

252
00:12:55,841 --> 00:12:57,643
- Do you have a trash bag?
- Right.

253
00:12:57,710 --> 00:12:59,578
- Give your trash to Mommy.
- Okay.

254
00:12:59,645 --> 00:13:01,247
Sweetheart, even if you grab a trash bag,

255
00:13:01,313 --> 00:13:04,183
I'm the one who ends up having
to throw everything out, you know?

256
00:13:04,683 --> 00:13:06,719
Just hand me your trash already.

257
00:13:07,219 --> 00:13:09,722
- Mom will handle it. Give it here.
- <i>Tomoaki is the best.</i>

258
00:13:09,789 --> 00:13:12,792
- <i>So this is his vibe.</i>
- <i>It's nice he loosened up.</i>

259
00:13:16,162 --> 00:13:18,230
He's hopeless when it comes to dating.

260
00:13:18,297 --> 00:13:20,132
- Yeah.
- He definitely is.

261
00:13:22,201 --> 00:13:24,603
Wait, what?
What do you mean, "Yeah," Ryuki?

262
00:13:24,670 --> 00:13:29,008
He's great at reading people, but
when it comes to romance, he's clueless.

263
00:13:29,074 --> 00:13:30,509
- Yeah, exactly.
- For real.

264
00:13:30,576 --> 00:13:33,112
Once I'm in a relationship,
I pretty much trust them.

265
00:13:33,179 --> 00:13:36,348
- So I don't really overthink that stuff.
- Right. You already know they like you.

266
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:37,483
Yeah, so…

267
00:13:37,550 --> 00:13:39,718
You just feel safe,
like they understand you.

268
00:13:39,785 --> 00:13:41,487
- Is he correct?
- Is that right?

269
00:13:41,554 --> 00:13:43,455
- I do feel that.
- See?

270
00:13:43,522 --> 00:13:45,191
What are you like when you get jealous?

271
00:13:45,758 --> 00:13:47,927
- Huh?
- How are you when you get jealous?

272
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:51,330
Like if they were just hanging out
and talking for a bit?

273
00:13:51,397 --> 00:13:53,766
- Say they went out to eat.
- When I'm in a relationship?

274
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,334
I don't get jealous.

275
00:13:55,401 --> 00:13:56,836
- Oh, you don't?
- You don't?

276
00:13:56,902 --> 00:13:58,771
- Even if they go out one-on-one?
- Huh?

277
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:00,439
Even if it's just the two of them?

278
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:03,976
And those two are, like,
talking like they're all buddy-buddy…

279
00:14:04,043 --> 00:14:06,979
But if it's someone I like and they
look like they're having fun, right?

280
00:14:07,046 --> 00:14:07,947
Then that's fine.

281
00:14:08,948 --> 00:14:10,916
- What are you, Buddha?
- Oh, you're that kind.

282
00:14:10,983 --> 00:14:12,885
- A bodhisattva?
- I don't relate to that at all.

283
00:14:12,952 --> 00:14:13,986
- Buddha?
- I don't get it…

284
00:14:14,053 --> 00:14:15,054
Reincarnation?

285
00:14:15,554 --> 00:14:16,422
Huh?

286
00:14:16,488 --> 00:14:19,358
You're such a nice guy. You are.

287
00:14:20,526 --> 00:14:23,629
- I guess.
- I don't know. I'm not that nice.

288
00:14:24,530 --> 00:14:25,631
Not that nice.

289
00:14:28,234 --> 00:14:31,270
Is it okay if your man is
on the slimmer side? Or more built?

290
00:14:32,071 --> 00:14:35,474
As long as he stays active,
it doesn't matter.

291
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,276
Hmm. What about his face?

292
00:14:37,343 --> 00:14:40,346
- I like stronger features.
- Aah.

293
00:14:40,412 --> 00:14:41,981
My own features are understated.

294
00:14:42,047 --> 00:14:45,517
- Understated?
- Do you have a preference?

295
00:14:45,584 --> 00:14:49,722
Me? Not someone super sharp-looking.

296
00:14:49,788 --> 00:14:50,923
More like

297
00:14:52,524 --> 00:14:54,293
someone who looks a bit sleepy.

298
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:56,128
- And cute.
- Sleepy?

299
00:14:56,195 --> 00:14:58,430
- I'm more into cute than cool-looking.
- Yeah.

300
00:14:58,497 --> 00:15:00,199
- <i>They're perfect.</i>
- <i>A match.</i>

301
00:15:00,266 --> 00:15:04,103
I think I like people who are smart.
Like, naturally smart.

302
00:15:04,169 --> 00:15:07,439
Someone who erases themselves

303
00:15:07,940 --> 00:15:10,809
and never does what they want,
just to please others…

304
00:15:10,876 --> 00:15:13,479
I don't see that as being a "good person."

305
00:15:13,545 --> 00:15:19,251
I don't either. Not at all.
Like, say he has a huge dream,

306
00:15:20,552 --> 00:15:23,188
and that dream would take him abroad.

307
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:27,359
"I could make this dream happen abroad,
but if you don't want me to go,

308
00:15:27,426 --> 00:15:30,362
I won't go and I'll stay here with you."

309
00:15:31,096 --> 00:15:32,631
- I don't like that.
- You don't, right?

310
00:15:32,698 --> 00:15:34,667
- I wouldn't either.
- I want to move forward.

311
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:38,270
- I'll go with him.
- That's what you mean, right?

312
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,874
I felt the same way.
I really didn't like that.

313
00:15:41,941 --> 00:15:44,510
It's not just that I don't like it,
I was disappointed.

314
00:15:44,576 --> 00:15:46,412
He's been talking
about that dream forever.

315
00:15:46,478 --> 00:15:48,714
It's finally coming true, so why…
You know?

316
00:15:48,781 --> 00:15:51,183
Before asking me what I think,

317
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:54,453
I wanted him to tell me, "Come with me.
I want you to come with me."

318
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,455
Or, "I'm going to make this happen
no matter what."

319
00:15:56,522 --> 00:15:58,057
We have to build both.

320
00:15:58,123 --> 00:16:01,894
Our own individual lives
and our life together.

321
00:16:04,897 --> 00:16:06,632
It's like building two homes.

322
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:07,700
Mmm.

323
00:16:11,437 --> 00:16:15,908
- These are the talks Taeheon wanted.
- To understand each other's values.

324
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,082
We're here!

325
00:16:23,582 --> 00:16:25,684
Whoa. That was a long ride, huh?

326
00:16:26,685 --> 00:16:28,487
- This place is gorgeous!
- Oh!

327
00:16:28,554 --> 00:16:30,923
- Let's check it out.
- I'm excited to see it.

328
00:16:31,457 --> 00:16:33,625
- Whoa, this is amazing. Beautiful.
- Wow.

329
00:16:33,692 --> 00:16:35,594
- Whoa.
- This is awesome.

330
00:16:36,095 --> 00:16:38,697
- There's even a fireplace.
- No way. That's cool.

331
00:16:39,431 --> 00:16:42,301
- This has to open, right?
- There's hidden doors everywhere.

332
00:16:42,801 --> 00:16:44,970
- This place is so nice.
- So nice.

333
00:16:45,871 --> 00:16:47,306
Oh, we can do the <i>löyly!</i>

334
00:16:47,373 --> 00:16:48,874
<i>Yatta!</i>

335
00:16:48,941 --> 00:16:51,377
You're really loving this!

336
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:53,312
Let's go check out the rooms.

337
00:16:53,379 --> 00:16:54,947
So stylish.

338
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,249
They're labeled one, two, three.

339
00:16:58,050 --> 00:17:00,919
- Okay, twin beds.
- For two.

340
00:17:00,986 --> 00:17:03,489
- Huh? They're all twins.
- Yeah, they're all twins.

341
00:17:03,555 --> 00:17:05,958
- Coming in.
- Maybe another room in the back?

342
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:07,292
Maybe one on this side.

343
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:09,495
- Oh, that's how it is?
- A single room?

344
00:17:09,561 --> 00:17:11,930
So it's two beds,
two beds, two beds, and a bunk bed.

345
00:17:11,997 --> 00:17:13,665
<i>Hard to decide who gets which room.</i>

346
00:17:13,732 --> 00:17:16,502
- <i>Who's going to share with who?</i>
- So how do we split?

347
00:17:17,002 --> 00:17:19,204
- Yeah. Any ideas?
- Uh…

348
00:17:19,271 --> 00:17:23,976
I kinda feel like
we're already on the same page.

349
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:26,311
But what do you think?

350
00:17:26,979 --> 00:17:29,381
So let's just say it out loud
and make it clear, then.

351
00:17:29,448 --> 00:17:30,416
Okay, room one then.

352
00:17:30,482 --> 00:17:31,784
Room one, okay. Then…

353
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:33,719
- I want two.
- What? Why?

354
00:17:33,786 --> 00:17:35,220
- I want one.
- Then me too.

355
00:17:35,287 --> 00:17:36,822
- Okay.
- Then I'm two.

356
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:39,058
- Room one, raise your hand.
- I still want two.

357
00:17:39,124 --> 00:17:40,859
- Room one, okay.
- I want that one.

358
00:17:40,926 --> 00:17:42,895
- Room two?
- Room two. Right.

359
00:17:42,961 --> 00:17:44,263
- Three?
- Okay?

360
00:17:44,329 --> 00:17:46,799
- Three's fine with me.
- We're in room three.

361
00:17:46,865 --> 00:17:48,867
Shall we drop our bags in the rooms?

362
00:17:48,934 --> 00:17:52,771
- <i>Hiroya didn't even get a chance.</i>
- <i>Yeah, he couldn't get a word in.</i>

363
00:17:56,608 --> 00:18:00,112
Which do you want?
In the back or the one in the front?

364
00:18:00,179 --> 00:18:01,580
I'll let you choose.

365
00:18:01,647 --> 00:18:03,248
- Bye-bye.
- Bye-bye.

366
00:18:03,315 --> 00:18:05,250
People can see right in, so be careful.

367
00:18:05,317 --> 00:18:08,253
- There are curtains, you know.
- We never close the curtains.

368
00:18:12,157 --> 00:18:13,992
<i>Oh! Are they pushing the beds together?</i>

369
00:18:14,059 --> 00:18:15,661
- <i>He is.</i>
- <i>That was fast.</i>

370
00:18:15,727 --> 00:18:18,097
<i>- Is that really the first thing they do?</i>
- <i>Seriously!</i>

371
00:18:18,163 --> 00:18:19,531
<i>First thing!</i>

372
00:18:19,598 --> 00:18:22,601
- So, what do you think?
- Huh? I just made it into one big bed.

373
00:18:22,668 --> 00:18:23,602
Whoa, already?

374
00:18:23,669 --> 00:18:26,038
We don't need this space here, right?

375
00:18:26,805 --> 00:18:29,808
- Oh… I like that.
- We don't need it.

376
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,443
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

377
00:18:34,713 --> 00:18:37,049
- I'm gonna head to the clinic.
- To the doctor?

378
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:40,119
Yeah, my ear hurts,
so I'm going to the ENT real quick.

379
00:18:40,185 --> 00:18:41,687
I'll step out for a moment.

380
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:44,523
- Take care.
- See you later.

381
00:18:44,590 --> 00:18:46,592
Even though Jo-Jo isn't here…

382
00:18:46,658 --> 00:18:48,660
- Why don't we toast?
- To Sapporo.

383
00:18:48,727 --> 00:18:50,762
- Enjoy it.
- Let's have a good time.

384
00:18:50,829 --> 00:18:52,564
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

385
00:18:53,065 --> 00:18:54,933
Shabu-shabu.

386
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:56,602
Napa cabbage? Can I put it in?

387
00:18:56,668 --> 00:19:00,105
- This shabu-shabu meat is so good.
- Mmm!

388
00:19:00,172 --> 00:19:01,406
- Good, right?
- So good.

389
00:19:01,473 --> 00:19:03,509
- Shabu-shabu's my favorite.
- Same.

390
00:19:03,575 --> 00:19:05,077
- Right?
- I like it better than sukiyaki.

391
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,745
Same. Better than <i>yakiniku </i>too.

392
00:19:06,812 --> 00:19:07,746
- Yep.
- Yep.

393
00:19:08,747 --> 00:19:10,616
- That's it.
- That's all from me.

394
00:19:11,884 --> 00:19:13,752
Then we can hit the sauna and stuff…

395
00:19:13,819 --> 00:19:14,853
Welcome back!

396
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:17,389
- We've been waiting before eating.
- You're eating already!

397
00:19:17,456 --> 00:19:18,757
- No!
- Looks good.

398
00:19:18,824 --> 00:19:21,660
- We saved some for you.
- Welcome… No, wait. I'm back.

399
00:19:22,694 --> 00:19:25,464
Oh, right. Jobu. I've been wanting
to go since you got here.

400
00:19:26,031 --> 00:19:27,666
There's something I want to talk about.

401
00:19:29,668 --> 00:19:32,738
So I wanna talk to Taeheon for a moment.

402
00:19:34,206 --> 00:19:35,741
Mm-hm. Let's talk.

403
00:19:35,807 --> 00:19:36,808
<i>Oh!</i>

404
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,777
- <i>Oh, ho ho.</i>
- <i>Well, of course.</i>

405
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:42,381
- Have fun.
- We'll be right back.

406
00:19:42,447 --> 00:19:44,583
- Thanks for the meal.
- Thank you.

407
00:19:44,650 --> 00:19:46,685
- See you later.
- Later, later.

408
00:19:53,792 --> 00:19:55,594
TANUKIKOJI 4

409
00:19:59,965 --> 00:20:01,600
- Hello.
- Hi.

410
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:04,536
- Oh!
- Oh, you noticed?

411
00:20:05,103 --> 00:20:11,343
I thought it'd be fun to enjoy Sapporo's
late-night parfait culture with you.

412
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:13,111
That's awesome. Thank you.

413
00:20:14,046 --> 00:20:16,949
- Thanks for coming out with me.
- <i>Ah, this is so nice.</i>

414
00:20:17,015 --> 00:20:19,184
- <i>That's a thing?</i>
- <i>Late-night parfaits.</i>

415
00:20:19,251 --> 00:20:22,187
What kind do you want,
more cream-heavy or more dessert-style?

416
00:20:22,254 --> 00:20:23,155
That's tough.

417
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,190
I think I'll go all-in on strawberry.

418
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:29,361
Thank you for waiting.
The strawberry <i>daifuku.</i>

419
00:20:29,428 --> 00:20:30,295
Wow.

420
00:20:31,029 --> 00:20:32,497
- Wow.
- Thank you.

421
00:20:32,564 --> 00:20:34,466
And this is the all-strawberry parfait.

422
00:20:34,533 --> 00:20:37,069
- This is just…
- This is crazy.

423
00:20:37,135 --> 00:20:39,705
- I'm so happy!
- Just take a big bite.

424
00:20:39,771 --> 00:20:41,773
- Big bite?
- Like…

425
00:20:47,846 --> 00:20:50,983
Nice. Nice, Taeheon.

426
00:20:52,851 --> 00:20:55,454
- <i>They're having fun.</i>
- <i>Yes, they are.</i>

427
00:20:55,954 --> 00:20:58,023
Is it good? Good.

428
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:00,759
- It just melts.
- Melts, huh?

429
00:21:02,694 --> 00:21:05,897
There's one thing
I've been wanting to ask you.

430
00:21:05,964 --> 00:21:07,232
What is it?

431
00:21:07,766 --> 00:21:08,867
Well…

432
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:11,370
- You remember the date event, right?
- Yeah.

433
00:21:11,436 --> 00:21:14,539
And you ended up choosing Jobu then.

434
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:16,742
- Yeah.
- And that's totally fine. Really, totally.

435
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:21,680
It's just…
you looked really conflicted then.

436
00:21:21,747 --> 00:21:22,681
- Right?
- Mm-hm.

437
00:21:23,515 --> 00:21:27,786
<i>I've just been curious.</i>
<i>What was on your mind back then?</i>

438
00:21:29,621 --> 00:21:31,423
Just wanted to ask you that.

439
00:21:31,490 --> 00:21:33,725
- I actually wanted to talk to you.
- Really?

440
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:35,427
- About that.
- I'm glad.

441
00:21:35,494 --> 00:21:38,530
Nice. That's a meaty question.

442
00:21:38,597 --> 00:21:43,468
The day before, we went to the museum
and then to that café.

443
00:21:43,535 --> 00:21:48,240
You shared your feelings
and you opened up so thoughtfully,

444
00:21:48,307 --> 00:21:49,941
and I was happy you did.

445
00:21:50,008 --> 00:21:53,979
But at that point, I still hadn't
sorted out my own feelings,

446
00:21:54,613 --> 00:21:58,450
and I was worried that
if I picked you right away,

447
00:21:58,517 --> 00:22:00,252
it would hurt you even more.

448
00:22:00,752 --> 00:22:03,255
To be honest, even if it hurt someone,

449
00:22:03,322 --> 00:22:06,391
I wasn't planning to change my decision,

450
00:22:07,559 --> 00:22:10,195
and that's me being completely blunt.

451
00:22:10,262 --> 00:22:13,165
So I kept wondering how to say that.

452
00:22:13,231 --> 00:22:14,266
- Oh.
- Mmm.

453
00:22:15,367 --> 00:22:18,804
Honestly,
I didn't know what the right way was.

454
00:22:19,538 --> 00:22:21,506
I'm glad I got to hear that. Thank you.

455
00:22:22,307 --> 00:22:25,477
The way you were trying
so hard not to hurt me…

456
00:22:25,544 --> 00:22:27,412
that really shows how kind you are.

457
00:22:27,479 --> 00:22:31,917
But you really don't have
to tiptoe around me.

458
00:22:32,417 --> 00:22:33,652
I…

459
00:22:34,886 --> 00:22:38,590
I love Jobu, I do, so much, as a friend.

460
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:42,861
He and I, for these two months,
even before you came,

461
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,430
we've shared

462
00:22:46,865 --> 00:22:49,835
tough moments,
happy moments, and sad ones together.

463
00:22:49,901 --> 00:22:51,336
We kept each other going.

464
00:22:51,403 --> 00:22:52,738
Yeah. I see.

465
00:22:54,573 --> 00:22:56,942
Yeah. So I just want him to be happy.

466
00:22:57,776 --> 00:22:59,311
From the bottom of my heart.

467
00:23:05,250 --> 00:23:07,519
- Hiroya!
- Wow, that's really mature.

468
00:23:07,586 --> 00:23:09,187
Those were some beautiful words.

469
00:23:09,254 --> 00:23:12,290
- Not many people can do that.
- So admirable.

470
00:23:12,357 --> 00:23:15,527
He's the one who's hurting the most.

471
00:23:15,594 --> 00:23:19,264
There was nothing fake about what he said.
It was just really genuine.

472
00:23:19,331 --> 00:23:22,868
- I didn't feel he was putting on anything.
- Not at all.

473
00:23:22,934 --> 00:23:28,006
Maybe the one who's changed the most
in this show is Hiroya, isn't it?

474
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:32,778
He used to get, you know,
misunderstood pretty easily.

475
00:23:34,479 --> 00:23:39,017
But now, he can be straightforward
without digging his heels in.

476
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:41,052
He's grown a lot.

477
00:23:42,487 --> 00:23:44,356
He wanted to draw a line for himself,

478
00:23:44,423 --> 00:23:46,425
and he went and created
that closure himself.

479
00:23:46,491 --> 00:23:47,859
I thought that was amazing.

480
00:23:47,926 --> 00:23:51,129
Even the way he asked was spot on.

481
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:53,365
- Instead of, "What do you think of me?"
- Yeah!

482
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:56,368
- He said, "What was on your mind then?"
- I thought that was so good.

483
00:23:56,435 --> 00:24:00,272
He even gave Taeheon
a beautiful way to turn him down.

484
00:24:00,338 --> 00:24:02,507
- Right? Amazing.
- Pure kindness.

485
00:24:02,574 --> 00:24:05,677
And Jobu pushing the beds
together right away was great too.

486
00:24:05,744 --> 00:24:07,446
- Just shove, shove, shove.
- Z-z-z-zip!

487
00:24:07,512 --> 00:24:09,648
The moment he saw it he went,
"I pushed them together."

488
00:24:09,714 --> 00:24:13,552
- He could just say it straight away.
- Like, "We don't need that side anyway."

489
00:24:13,618 --> 00:24:15,253
- That vibe is great.
- It was good.

490
00:24:17,088 --> 00:24:18,156
Morning.

491
00:24:18,223 --> 00:24:21,827
So… I actually have a little proposal.

492
00:24:22,594 --> 00:24:25,730
Since today is the last day
of our Sapporo trip,

493
00:24:26,231 --> 00:24:28,333
and I'd like to end it the right way,

494
00:24:29,334 --> 00:24:33,505
I was hoping I could
spend the day with Huwei.

495
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:37,409
Would that be okay?

496
00:24:39,110 --> 00:24:40,378
Yeah, that's fine.

497
00:24:46,284 --> 00:24:49,120
I wanna spend the day with Jo-Jo.

498
00:24:49,187 --> 00:24:50,188
Go for it.

499
00:24:51,590 --> 00:24:53,058
Then let's do that.

500
00:24:53,124 --> 00:24:54,993
- Are you okay with that?
- Of course.

501
00:24:56,661 --> 00:24:57,996
See you this evening.

502
00:24:58,964 --> 00:25:01,800
- Have fun. See you later.
- We're off. Yeah.

503
00:25:05,804 --> 00:25:07,506
- See you later.
- Bye.

504
00:25:09,207 --> 00:25:11,309
- Have a good time.
- We're heading out.

505
00:25:11,376 --> 00:25:12,577
- See you! Ow!
- Bye.

506
00:25:12,644 --> 00:25:15,113
- That looked like it hurt. Bye.
- Catch you later.

507
00:25:16,982 --> 00:25:18,950
ODORI PARK

508
00:25:22,988 --> 00:25:24,689
- Here.
- Thanks.

509
00:25:27,626 --> 00:25:28,860
Hello. Hello.

510
00:25:28,927 --> 00:25:31,663
- Wow, this is cool.
- Hello, please have a seat.

511
00:25:31,730 --> 00:25:36,468
Each fragrance is built in three layers,
top, middle, and last.

512
00:25:37,168 --> 00:25:40,672
We have 25 varieties
for you to choose from.

513
00:25:40,739 --> 00:25:42,374
There's gonna be one you won't like.

514
00:25:43,275 --> 00:25:45,443
Scents are really about
personal preference, right?

515
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:47,879
Isn't it hard to choose one
for someone else?

516
00:25:47,946 --> 00:25:49,047
Well, actually…

517
00:25:49,114 --> 00:25:51,049
Should we each make one for the other?

518
00:25:51,116 --> 00:25:52,083
For each other.

519
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:55,153
Shall we?
Okay, I'll picture you and start blending.

520
00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:58,857
Mmm.

521
00:26:00,825 --> 00:26:02,027
Mmm.

522
00:26:03,128 --> 00:26:04,996
I don't usually wear perfume.

523
00:26:06,932 --> 00:26:09,367
- Okay.
- Oh. Oh!

524
00:26:09,434 --> 00:26:12,003
You can design a label at the end.

525
00:26:13,104 --> 00:26:15,974
Oh, wow! This looks great.

526
00:26:16,675 --> 00:26:20,345
This is the perfume I made.

527
00:26:21,413 --> 00:26:22,514
Here you go.

528
00:26:25,383 --> 00:26:27,886
- It's called Job's Special.
- Oh!

529
00:26:28,453 --> 00:26:30,221
I just put my own name in it.

530
00:26:30,288 --> 00:26:31,990
- I see.
- Yep.

531
00:26:33,725 --> 00:26:35,660
- It smells like coffee.
- You get that?

532
00:26:35,727 --> 00:26:37,729
- Mmm.
- You love coffee.

533
00:26:37,796 --> 00:26:40,398
And it has that Green Room vibe, right?

534
00:26:40,465 --> 00:26:41,466
- Approved.
- Approved!

535
00:26:41,533 --> 00:26:42,701
<i>Glad to hear it!</i>

536
00:26:42,767 --> 00:26:43,635
Thank you.

537
00:26:43,702 --> 00:26:45,837
This is the one I made.

538
00:26:46,638 --> 00:26:47,572
What does it mean?

539
00:26:47,639 --> 00:26:52,944
I named it "unfold within,"
meaning it opens from the inside. Yeah?

540
00:26:53,011 --> 00:26:54,012
From the inside?

541
00:26:54,512 --> 00:26:56,448
Not from the outside, from the inside.

542
00:26:56,514 --> 00:26:58,483
- Inside.
- It opens within.

543
00:26:59,751 --> 00:27:01,119
You know?

544
00:27:03,388 --> 00:27:05,056
Oh, that smells so good.

545
00:27:05,123 --> 00:27:07,392
- There is a story behind it.
- A story?

546
00:27:07,459 --> 00:27:08,693
- Yeah.
- Tell me.

547
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:11,162
I added cilantro, something I hate.

548
00:27:11,229 --> 00:27:12,497
- Oh?
- I hate eating it.

549
00:27:12,564 --> 00:27:15,033
But when I smelled it,
it actually smelled really nice.

550
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:17,068
Like our first coffee truck shift.

551
00:27:18,970 --> 00:27:23,775
So, for this, things didn't unfold
so well between us at first.

552
00:27:23,842 --> 00:27:27,145
But then I started adding
the scents I love.

553
00:27:27,212 --> 00:27:28,780
- <i>So romantic.</i>
- <i>So cool.</i>

554
00:27:28,847 --> 00:27:30,682
<i>Impressive, Taeheon.</i>

555
00:27:35,387 --> 00:27:36,921
- Can I ask?
- Yeah.

556
00:27:36,988 --> 00:27:39,457
When you cooked for me
and had dinner outside,

557
00:27:39,958 --> 00:27:43,428
when you told me that day…

558
00:27:43,495 --> 00:27:44,329
Mmm.

559
00:27:45,597 --> 00:27:50,635
Um, what made you decide
to tell me that night?

560
00:27:50,702 --> 00:27:52,470
Hmm…

561
00:27:52,537 --> 00:27:54,272
At that time,

562
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:59,511
I wasn't really planning
to say I like you.

563
00:28:00,011 --> 00:28:01,646
- Hmm?
- Yeah.

564
00:28:01,713 --> 00:28:04,749
But I was really nervous

565
00:28:05,984 --> 00:28:07,519
while I was cooking.

566
00:28:08,019 --> 00:28:12,257
But I also realized
I was really excited to cook for you.

567
00:28:13,224 --> 00:28:17,662
And when you actually tried my cooking…
I was just so happy.

568
00:28:17,729 --> 00:28:22,233
That kind of thing was a first for me.
Watching you eat the lasagna I made…

569
00:28:24,269 --> 00:28:26,137
The words just came out naturally.

570
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:27,138
Yeah.

571
00:28:27,205 --> 00:28:31,743
So, I wasn't planning
on telling you that I liked you.

572
00:28:31,810 --> 00:28:32,944
Mmm.

573
00:28:34,212 --> 00:28:37,449
That's how I ended up saying that.
It came out naturally.

574
00:28:37,515 --> 00:28:38,850
Well… Yeah.

575
00:28:38,917 --> 00:28:40,518
In that moment.

576
00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:45,523
Um… up until then…

577
00:28:45,590 --> 00:28:47,992
Well, if it were me,

578
00:28:48,593 --> 00:28:51,229
I would've had more serious conversations

579
00:28:51,296 --> 00:28:53,732
and gotten to know the other person

580
00:28:54,499 --> 00:28:57,535
better before feeling certain, but,

581
00:28:58,903 --> 00:29:04,375
honestly, I felt like we hadn't talked
about enough things to reach that stage.

582
00:29:05,610 --> 00:29:09,481
And yet, you put it into words,

583
00:29:09,981 --> 00:29:11,750
my heart skipped a beat.

584
00:29:13,952 --> 00:29:16,354
I thought I might have jumped the gun.

585
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,389
I didn't expect to blurt it out either.

586
00:29:18,456 --> 00:29:22,994
The mood in that moment made me want
to say it, so it just came out naturally.

587
00:29:24,295 --> 00:29:25,964
I wonder if it was too soon.

588
00:29:26,698 --> 00:29:28,767
I thought… And then later,

589
00:29:28,833 --> 00:29:32,170
you said, "But there is
so much we haven't talked about."

590
00:29:32,237 --> 00:29:33,872
You said, "I want
to know more about you."

591
00:29:33,938 --> 00:29:36,207
And I thought,
"Yeah, I guess that's true."

592
00:29:36,274 --> 00:29:39,644
There are parts of you that I don't know
yet, and parts of me you don't know.

593
00:29:39,711 --> 00:29:41,279
That's the truth.

594
00:29:41,346 --> 00:29:44,249
It might have been too… too soon.

595
00:29:44,315 --> 00:29:47,318
That's what I thought as we were talking.

596
00:29:47,819 --> 00:29:48,887
Yeah.

597
00:29:51,389 --> 00:29:54,058
But we've talked
about different things since then.

598
00:29:56,528 --> 00:29:58,897
But my feelings haven't changed. Mmm.

599
00:29:58,963 --> 00:29:59,831
Mmm.

600
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:11,042
I wonder what everyone else is doing.

601
00:30:11,109 --> 00:30:13,011
Yeah, I hope they're getting along.

602
00:30:13,578 --> 00:30:15,446
- I'm sure!
- I'd be surprised if they're fighting.

603
00:30:15,513 --> 00:30:18,917
From what I saw this morning,
I think I'd be upset if I were Bomi.

604
00:30:18,983 --> 00:30:20,185
What do you mean?

605
00:30:20,718 --> 00:30:25,490
Bomi went out of his way to say he wanted
to go out with Huwei in front of everyone,

606
00:30:25,557 --> 00:30:28,359
but he was like, "Yeah, that's fine."

607
00:30:28,893 --> 00:30:31,229
Like… he'd be like that to anyone.

608
00:30:31,729 --> 00:30:34,632
- Oh, you mean even if I had asked him?
- Mm, mm-hmm.

609
00:30:35,033 --> 00:30:36,868
He'd probably say, "Yeah, that's fine."

610
00:30:36,935 --> 00:30:39,437
But, you know, in my opinion,

611
00:30:39,504 --> 00:30:42,540
if someone says
they want to go out with you,

612
00:30:43,174 --> 00:30:46,644
you should give a real answer,
instead of just saying, "That's fine."

613
00:30:48,379 --> 00:30:52,317
But I still think
he really likes Bomi, though.

614
00:30:52,383 --> 00:30:53,384
Mmm.

615
00:30:54,185 --> 00:30:56,421
Well, I hope
he makes up his mind in the end.

616
00:30:57,322 --> 00:30:58,790
Thank you very much.

617
00:30:58,857 --> 00:31:01,659
- Matcha latte. Coffee crema.
- Matcha looks great.

618
00:31:01,726 --> 00:31:03,161
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

619
00:31:04,529 --> 00:31:06,865
I wonder how
the three who left are doing.

620
00:31:07,799 --> 00:31:09,634
- Hope they're good.
- I wanna see them.

621
00:31:10,134 --> 00:31:11,803
I wonder what they're doing.

622
00:31:13,404 --> 00:31:15,640
Maybe they're fighting like crazy.

623
00:31:20,511 --> 00:31:24,482
Today, you'll be making handmade rings.

624
00:31:24,549 --> 00:31:28,820
So of course, both of you will
do the crafting yourselves.

625
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:31,356
Which fingers will you wear the rings on?

626
00:31:31,422 --> 00:31:35,793
Huwei, you'll wear yours on
your right ring finger to bring stability,

627
00:31:35,860 --> 00:31:38,396
and I'll wear mine on
my left ring finger to deepen our bond.

628
00:31:38,463 --> 00:31:41,065
- So, stability and bond.
- Okay, got it.

629
00:31:41,933 --> 00:31:43,401
- Have you decided?
- We have.

630
00:31:43,468 --> 00:31:44,802
- You have?
- We have.

631
00:31:44,869 --> 00:31:47,839
That's great!
Well then, let's start crafting.

632
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:50,875
To begin, please decide if you would like
to make each other's rings.

633
00:31:50,942 --> 00:31:53,311
- Or your own rings?
- Each other's!

634
00:31:53,378 --> 00:31:54,746
- Each other's it is.
- Okay.

635
00:31:54,812 --> 00:31:57,015
- Are you okay with that?
- Yes, we're good.

636
00:31:59,350 --> 00:32:02,153
<i>I bet Huwei's going</i>
<i>to be really good at this.</i>

637
00:32:09,761 --> 00:32:12,764
The lighting changes
with every strike of the hammer.

638
00:32:13,865 --> 00:32:14,966
- Is that how?
- Yes!

639
00:32:15,033 --> 00:32:16,935
That's how the projection mapping works.

640
00:32:18,002 --> 00:32:21,005
Oh, you're right. Wow. This is fun.

641
00:32:21,072 --> 00:32:23,708
<i>Is the secret</i>

642
00:32:24,208 --> 00:32:26,844
<i>I don't wanna wait</i>

643
00:32:26,911 --> 00:32:31,649
<i>Can you hear what I've been thinkin'? </i>

644
00:32:31,716 --> 00:32:33,351
<i>In my heart</i>

645
00:32:34,385 --> 00:32:35,386
It's done.

646
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:39,924
- Thank you so much for waiting.
- Thank you.

647
00:32:39,991 --> 00:32:41,559
Here are your finished rings.

648
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,461
- Oh, wow, so cute.
- So cute.

649
00:32:44,262 --> 00:32:45,730
They look great.

650
00:32:52,036 --> 00:32:55,173
- Great work, guys.
- Thank you very much.

651
00:32:55,239 --> 00:32:57,475
- That's it for the crafting.
- That was fun.

652
00:32:57,542 --> 00:33:00,178
- I loved it.
- Really? Thank you so much.

653
00:33:04,615 --> 00:33:07,118
- Oh, the penguins are so cute.
- So cute.

654
00:33:07,185 --> 00:33:08,920
So that's how they swim?

655
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,123
- It's like they're flying.
- Mmm.

656
00:33:15,893 --> 00:33:17,595
I didn't know how penguins sound.

657
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:19,397
Right?

658
00:33:24,068 --> 00:33:26,637
- Today was fun.
- It was fun.

659
00:33:31,809 --> 00:33:33,011
By the way…

660
00:33:34,879 --> 00:33:36,581
These past few days…

661
00:33:37,648 --> 00:33:39,784
It's not exactly jealousy, but…

662
00:33:40,785 --> 00:33:44,522
…I had a feeling kind of like that
for a short while.

663
00:33:44,589 --> 00:33:45,523
Why?

664
00:33:45,590 --> 00:33:47,125
"Why?"

665
00:33:47,191 --> 00:33:49,761
- That's so Huwei.
- He has no idea.

666
00:33:49,827 --> 00:33:53,297
I mean, you bought us
souvenirs from your trip, right?

667
00:33:53,364 --> 00:33:54,565
- Mmm.
- Well…

668
00:33:55,266 --> 00:33:57,502
- I was really waiting for you.
- Mmm.

669
00:33:57,568 --> 00:33:59,337
- I really wanted to see you.
- Mmm.

670
00:33:59,404 --> 00:34:03,241
When you finally came back,
I was super happy.

671
00:34:04,042 --> 00:34:07,812
But the first thing you said was, "Oh,
I thought Ryuki would like to have this."

672
00:34:08,913 --> 00:34:12,083
- Well, he didn't…
- Like, "I bought you some dried durian."

673
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:13,084
Yeah, yeah.

674
00:34:13,151 --> 00:34:18,656
Well, the gift itself doesn't matter.
Like, you said you wanted to see me.

675
00:34:19,757 --> 00:34:24,095
But if it were me, I'd want
to buy something and give it to you.

676
00:34:24,162 --> 00:34:26,831
Like, I really felt that way

677
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:30,334
when I went back to Kansai,
because I missed you.

678
00:34:30,401 --> 00:34:33,638
But I didn't feel like you felt that way.

679
00:34:34,405 --> 00:34:36,441
- So it made me sad.
- Mmm.

680
00:34:36,507 --> 00:34:39,544
Yeah. That's how I kind of felt.

681
00:34:41,412 --> 00:34:42,713
Actually…

682
00:34:44,015 --> 00:34:46,150
I tried to buy you something,
but nothing felt right.

683
00:34:47,118 --> 00:34:48,719
So I didn't buy anything.

684
00:34:50,555 --> 00:34:52,557
- Then you should've told me.
- Hmm?

685
00:34:52,623 --> 00:34:54,092
You should've told me that.

686
00:34:54,158 --> 00:34:56,928
But there's no point in telling you
that if I didn't get you anything.

687
00:34:56,994 --> 00:34:58,496
Well, that's true, but

688
00:34:58,996 --> 00:35:00,231
I just thought

689
00:35:01,632 --> 00:35:03,367
maybe you weren't thinking about me.

690
00:35:03,868 --> 00:35:05,436
I really missed you, though.

691
00:35:06,504 --> 00:35:07,438
Mmm.

692
00:35:14,912 --> 00:35:18,382
When we leave here…
what do you see for us?

693
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:20,218
- <i>Whoa!</i>
- <i>Cut to the core!</i>

694
00:35:20,284 --> 00:35:21,752
You mean… us?

695
00:35:25,423 --> 00:35:27,358
I mean, now we both…

696
00:35:31,262 --> 00:35:34,165
kind of like each other, you know?

697
00:35:37,034 --> 00:35:38,469
That's what it feels like.

698
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:44,008
But after we leave,

699
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:47,745
I wonder if we'll still want
to see each other.

700
00:35:50,548 --> 00:35:54,018
I actually think the real beginning
starts after we leave.

701
00:35:55,586 --> 00:35:56,587
For me.

702
00:35:57,622 --> 00:35:59,190
- Right.
- Mmm.

703
00:36:03,861 --> 00:36:05,763
I wonder what it means to be together.

704
00:36:06,764 --> 00:36:08,466
To be together? What do you mean?

705
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:11,502
- I wonder what it means to be together.
- Wonder what it means to be together?

706
00:36:14,305 --> 00:36:16,607
What I think it means to be together…

707
00:36:16,674 --> 00:36:19,644
When I really think about
my life up to this point,

708
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:24,982
I've never really faced someone
I had feelings for head-on in my life.

709
00:36:25,049 --> 00:36:26,384
You're the first person for this.

710
00:36:26,450 --> 00:36:29,554
I don't think I'll ever have another
chance to spend every day with someone

711
00:36:29,620 --> 00:36:31,088
and focus on them.

712
00:36:32,490 --> 00:36:35,259
That's why this whole experience
has been very special to me.

713
00:36:36,060 --> 00:36:40,331
So, it made me want to keep building
a relationship like this.

714
00:36:41,332 --> 00:36:43,134
Not quite like family yet,

715
00:36:43,201 --> 00:36:47,471
but I want to be someone
that important to you eventually.

716
00:36:48,940 --> 00:36:53,377
I want us to have a relationship
where we can talk about anything.

717
00:36:55,112 --> 00:36:59,617
I just wondered if we'd be able to
face things together from here on.

718
00:36:59,684 --> 00:37:00,685
Mmm.

719
00:37:01,819 --> 00:37:02,720
But

720
00:37:04,222 --> 00:37:07,158
as for your view on being together,

721
00:37:09,160 --> 00:37:12,630
I thought it was pretty similar to mine.

722
00:37:13,130 --> 00:37:17,068
<i>With love</i>

723
00:37:17,134 --> 00:37:21,772
<i>I can change the sky above</i>

724
00:37:21,839 --> 00:37:26,944
<i>And rise a little higher</i>

725
00:37:27,011 --> 00:37:29,413
<i>Until the sun </i>

726
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:34,418
<i>Feels closer again </i>

727
00:37:35,786 --> 00:37:38,022
Even the jellyfish are saying,
"Thank goodness."

728
00:37:38,089 --> 00:37:40,391
Don't make us so nervous!

729
00:37:40,458 --> 00:37:42,593
- Please stop!
- Oh, gosh!

730
00:37:42,660 --> 00:37:46,197
Huwei does have moments
where he throws people off.

731
00:37:46,264 --> 00:37:48,266
- Sometimes, right?
- That's true.

732
00:37:48,332 --> 00:37:50,434
I feel like he's just
a very straightforward person.

733
00:37:50,501 --> 00:37:52,536
I don't think Huwei is
the type to test people.

734
00:37:52,603 --> 00:37:53,771
Exactly.

735
00:37:53,838 --> 00:37:55,673
So, Bomi just needs to get used to that.

736
00:37:55,740 --> 00:38:00,311
I mean, he was actually leading him really
well at first, right?

737
00:38:00,378 --> 00:38:03,080
- If he really likes…
- I think Bomi can pull it off.

738
00:38:03,147 --> 00:38:04,415
- True.
- Right? I think so too.

739
00:38:04,482 --> 00:38:05,750
Do we really need souvenirs?

740
00:38:05,816 --> 00:38:08,352
- I'd definitely want a souvenir.
- Huh, you would?

741
00:38:08,419 --> 00:38:10,588
If I were in a similar
relationship with someone

742
00:38:10,655 --> 00:38:12,890
and they traveled somewhere
without bringing back a gift,

743
00:38:12,957 --> 00:38:15,226
I'd be like, "Oh, okay."

744
00:38:15,293 --> 00:38:17,228
- Definitely.
- Can it be anything?

745
00:38:17,295 --> 00:38:19,497
- Anything is fine.
- Even a magnet for the fridge?

746
00:38:19,563 --> 00:38:21,799
Yeah, even a keychain
that says "Megumi" on it.

747
00:38:21,866 --> 00:38:23,901
That's fine, that's enough.

748
00:38:23,968 --> 00:38:27,505
It would make me very happy to know
that they were thinking of me.

749
00:38:27,571 --> 00:38:30,041
- As a token.
- Yeah. Well, what do you think?

750
00:38:30,107 --> 00:38:31,942
I'm actually okay without it…

751
00:38:32,009 --> 00:38:33,577
Betraying me all of a sudden?

752
00:38:34,712 --> 00:38:36,213
What's with you?

753
00:38:37,014 --> 00:38:38,249
Unbelievable!

754
00:38:38,316 --> 00:38:40,985
- So souvenirs aren't necessary?
- What the heck?

755
00:38:41,485 --> 00:38:44,322
- I don't mind no souvenirs.
- It's so tricky.

756
00:38:46,023 --> 00:38:47,992
There's one last thing
I want to talk about.

757
00:38:48,059 --> 00:38:48,893
Sure.

758
00:38:49,593 --> 00:38:54,265
I still don't know how I should,
you know, come out.

759
00:38:55,566 --> 00:38:58,536
I lost my mom when I was in kindergarten.

760
00:38:59,870 --> 00:39:03,607
And after that, my dad raised me

761
00:39:04,675 --> 00:39:06,477
all by himself until now.

762
00:39:07,712 --> 00:39:09,347
I can't bring myself to think,

763
00:39:09,413 --> 00:39:13,150
"If he doesn't accept me,
then that's that."

764
00:39:14,618 --> 00:39:18,923
I used to think that sharing this
with people was pointless

765
00:39:18,989 --> 00:39:21,926
because their circumstances
weren't the same.

766
00:39:21,992 --> 00:39:24,228
But after talking about it here,

767
00:39:24,895 --> 00:39:27,164
it made me think, um…

768
00:39:27,665 --> 00:39:30,434
"It's going to be okay because
everyone's here for me."

769
00:39:31,168 --> 00:39:32,403
<i>It feels good.</i>

770
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:35,773
So that's why I want to talk about it.

771
00:39:36,340 --> 00:39:38,109
So you have the will to tell him.

772
00:39:38,175 --> 00:39:39,310
- At least that's clear.
- Yeah.

773
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:40,544
That hasn't changed?

774
00:39:40,611 --> 00:39:43,547
After thinking about everything,
do you still definitely want to come out?

775
00:39:43,614 --> 00:39:45,483
I want it to come from me.

776
00:39:47,184 --> 00:39:51,856
You know, I've always wanted
to come out to my parents too.

777
00:39:52,423 --> 00:39:58,329
But I felt like it's unfair to expect
an answer from them right on the spot.

778
00:39:59,096 --> 00:40:02,767
So I decided to come out to them
with a letter.

779
00:40:04,001 --> 00:40:06,637
I see. A letter…

780
00:40:06,704 --> 00:40:09,106
And to share a slightly
different perspective,

781
00:40:09,173 --> 00:40:13,077
I don't think coming out ends
the moment you tell them.

782
00:40:13,844 --> 00:40:17,948
It is something you face with
your family over a lifetime.

783
00:40:18,449 --> 00:40:23,387
My family all accepted
it in different ways.

784
00:40:24,488 --> 00:40:28,793
My dad showed his support
by cheering me on like, "You've got this!"

785
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:32,696
My older sister said, "I'm sorry
I couldn't notice your struggle,"

786
00:40:32,763 --> 00:40:34,231
from a place of worry.

787
00:40:35,032 --> 00:40:38,736
My brother is younger,
so he was like, "What's the big deal?"

788
00:40:39,670 --> 00:40:42,039
And my mom
thought through so carefully,

789
00:40:43,641 --> 00:40:46,310
and she shows it through
her actions rather than words.

790
00:40:46,877 --> 00:40:49,447
- Like, "Did you see that LGBT movie?"
- Mmm.

791
00:40:50,815 --> 00:40:54,084
Or, "That author's book is really good,
so I'll lend it to you."

792
00:40:54,151 --> 00:40:55,553
She says things like that.

793
00:40:56,053 --> 00:40:58,355
So it's been five or six years,

794
00:40:58,422 --> 00:41:03,093
but my mom has been working on overcoming
her biases and trying to accept me,

795
00:41:03,160 --> 00:41:04,662
and I'm really grateful for that.

796
00:41:05,529 --> 00:41:06,931
So, in response,

797
00:41:07,798 --> 00:41:10,134
we also have to be mindful of that.

798
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:12,403
Over the course of life,

799
00:41:14,171 --> 00:41:18,008
I think you have to keep showing him,
it's not a bad thing.

800
00:41:18,075 --> 00:41:20,444
And "I'm living happily."

801
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:26,617
I think it might be good to view
coming out in the long term like that.

802
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:28,586
- Mmm.
- I'm rooting for you.

803
00:41:33,524 --> 00:41:35,926
Make the choice. You won't regret…

804
00:41:35,993 --> 00:41:37,161
Well, whatever you choose…

805
00:41:37,228 --> 00:41:39,930
- Whatever you choose.
- There's a chance you regret it.

806
00:41:39,997 --> 00:41:42,833
But I think it's best to go with
the option you'll regret the least.

807
00:41:42,900 --> 00:41:46,570
And you might feel sorry
about it. I felt that way a lot too.

808
00:41:46,637 --> 00:41:52,009
But when I started thinking about
how I wanted to show up for my parents,

809
00:41:52,076 --> 00:41:55,679
all of that guilt I'd been carrying
started to fade away.

810
00:41:56,180 --> 00:41:59,483
I think what really matters
is how much you face yourself

811
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:01,051
and arrive at your own answer.

812
00:42:01,118 --> 00:42:04,288
Yeah, um… so…

813
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:07,925
- <i>Hmm?</i>
- <i>What's going on?</i>

814
00:42:07,992 --> 00:42:09,126
<i>What happened?</i>

815
00:42:14,131 --> 00:42:15,666
Hm? Yeah?

816
00:42:16,567 --> 00:42:20,204
- What's the matter?
- I'm fine. I just wanted fresh air.

817
00:42:20,704 --> 00:42:23,941
- You should've told me.
- I'm going back. I'm going back now.

818
00:42:24,708 --> 00:42:25,876
- You okay?
- I'm fine.

819
00:42:25,943 --> 00:42:27,978
- Is something wrong?
- No, nothing.

820
00:42:28,646 --> 00:42:30,948
- Hmm?
- Nothing, it's really nothing.

821
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:32,416
- Really?
- Yeah.

822
00:42:33,651 --> 00:42:34,685
Let's go back.

823
00:42:36,220 --> 00:42:37,888
- Something wrong?
- Nothing!

824
00:42:37,955 --> 00:42:39,089
Is it because your ears hurt?

825
00:42:39,156 --> 00:42:41,825
My ears don't hurt.
I'm fine. Nothing's wrong.

826
00:42:42,660 --> 00:42:44,895
- <i>"Nothing" is worrying.</i>
- Like my father.

827
00:42:44,962 --> 00:42:46,564
<i>Yeah, really.</i>

828
00:42:46,630 --> 00:42:50,067
So I still think that
I wasn't good enough as a son.

829
00:42:53,370 --> 00:42:55,606
Hiroya's words really hit me today.

830
00:42:56,173 --> 00:42:59,009
- Let's take a picture of today.
- What's with you, Bomi…

831
00:42:59,076 --> 00:43:01,612
Ba… Ba, Bami…
Oh, I tripped over your name.

832
00:43:02,980 --> 00:43:05,316
You look way too sexy with your bangs.

833
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:09,553
- Look at Bomi's bangs! Look at him!
- Everyone, a picture.

834
00:43:13,724 --> 00:43:16,160
But we looked so cute
in front of the fireplace.

835
00:43:16,226 --> 00:43:17,394
I'll tell you later.

836
00:43:19,029 --> 00:43:20,164
Come over here.

837
00:43:21,265 --> 00:43:23,567
One plus two is N!

838
00:43:23,634 --> 00:43:25,803
<i>He's not going to him!</i>

839
00:43:25,869 --> 00:43:28,906
<i>What happened?</i>
<i>I wonder what happened and when?</i>

840
00:43:29,673 --> 00:43:31,609
- Everyone…
- Can we take a selfie?

841
00:43:31,675 --> 00:43:34,078
We looked so good
in front of the fireplace.

842
00:43:36,347 --> 00:43:38,916
While listening to everyone
talking about coming out,

843
00:43:38,983 --> 00:43:43,220
I realized my situation was completely
different from everyone else's.

844
00:43:43,287 --> 00:43:47,324
I didn't even need to come out
because of the way things were at home.

845
00:43:47,391 --> 00:43:50,160
So I never had to worry about it at all.

846
00:43:50,227 --> 00:43:53,764
<i>That's why listening</i>
<i>to everyone's story really weighed on me.</i>

847
00:43:54,765 --> 00:43:56,600
It was different from my experience.

848
00:43:56,667 --> 00:43:59,370
And, like, I couldn't
say anything in that situation.

849
00:44:00,371 --> 00:44:03,440
Then I started
to feel really uncomfortable,

850
00:44:03,507 --> 00:44:05,909
and the mood was so heavy,

851
00:44:05,976 --> 00:44:08,245
so I decided to go outside
for some fresh air.

852
00:44:10,014 --> 00:44:11,482
So I went outside.

853
00:44:12,650 --> 00:44:17,821
I thought he could have at least
told me he was going to our room,

854
00:44:17,888 --> 00:44:19,256
so I went after him.

855
00:44:19,323 --> 00:44:22,593
He was trying to brush things off
by saying, "I'm fine,"

856
00:44:22,660 --> 00:44:25,029
and that's when I got frustrated a little.

857
00:44:25,095 --> 00:44:26,730
A little while ago,

858
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:32,269
Taeheon had said that
I have a habit of dodging serious talk.

859
00:44:32,336 --> 00:44:33,771
And he had said something like,

860
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:40,310
"When I tell you I want to talk seriously,
I need you to open up with me."

861
00:44:40,377 --> 00:44:43,147
<i>Taeheon went out of his way</i>
<i>to check on me,</i>

862
00:44:43,213 --> 00:44:46,684
<i>but I didn't say anything</i>
<i>and just brushed it off like usual,</i>

863
00:44:46,750 --> 00:44:47,985
<i>saying, "I'm fine, I'm fine."</i>

864
00:44:48,052 --> 00:44:49,987
I realized that wasn't right.

865
00:44:50,721 --> 00:44:52,923
That's why I went back to our room.

866
00:44:53,424 --> 00:44:56,527
- This is difficult.
- Neither of them is wrong, but…

867
00:44:56,593 --> 00:44:58,729
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

868
00:44:58,796 --> 00:45:00,731
- Goodnight.
- See you tomorrow.

869
00:45:03,667 --> 00:45:06,003
- <i>What will happen?</i>
- <i>Stride, stride, stride.</i>

870
00:45:06,070 --> 00:45:09,006
- <i>They are in the same room.</i>
- <i>And their beds are together.</i>

871
00:45:19,316 --> 00:45:20,217
<i>What?</i>

872
00:45:24,154 --> 00:45:26,090
<i>No!</i>

873
00:45:28,926 --> 00:45:30,761
<i>Princess, isn't that going too far?</i>

874
00:45:30,828 --> 00:45:32,629
<i>He didn't have to do that.</i>

875
00:45:55,018 --> 00:45:56,820
No!

876
00:45:56,887 --> 00:45:58,856
This is difficult.

877
00:45:58,922 --> 00:46:00,424
Did it have to get this bad?

878
00:46:00,491 --> 00:46:02,993
Depending on the person,
that "I'm fine, I'm fine"

879
00:46:03,060 --> 00:46:06,196
might come across
as shutting down communication.

880
00:46:06,263 --> 00:46:09,166
But in the moment, it's a bit hard
to put feelings into words.

881
00:46:09,233 --> 00:46:13,070
It's hard to explain yourself
when you're feeling overwhelmed.

882
00:46:13,137 --> 00:46:14,404
It's so difficult, isn't it?

883
00:46:14,471 --> 00:46:18,575
But up until then, Jobu had been
dodging conversation for some time,

884
00:46:18,642 --> 00:46:21,078
and Taeheon was feeling,
"Just talk to me already."

885
00:46:21,145 --> 00:46:23,313
- Well, true.
- So he was probably like, "Again?"

886
00:46:23,380 --> 00:46:24,381
"This is getting tiring."

887
00:46:24,448 --> 00:46:26,617
It was right after Jobu said
he'd start opening up, too.

888
00:46:26,683 --> 00:46:28,719
- That's why he exploded.
- Might be.

889
00:46:28,786 --> 00:46:31,555
Taeheon only gets upset
precisely because he likes Jobu, right?

890
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:32,456
Right.

891
00:46:32,523 --> 00:46:36,193
And when Taeheon tried to pull the bed,
it barely budged, right?

892
00:46:36,960 --> 00:46:38,796
That means the bed must be really heavy.

893
00:46:38,862 --> 00:46:41,265
- But Jobu moved it easily. Bam, right?
- Bam!

894
00:46:41,331 --> 00:46:44,668
I realize now that Jobu was really eager
to put their beds together.

895
00:46:46,403 --> 00:46:47,271
Really badly.

896
00:46:47,337 --> 00:46:49,273
- So true!
- It required a lot of strength.

897
00:46:49,339 --> 00:46:52,509
And Ryuki asked for advice
about coming out.

898
00:46:52,576 --> 00:46:54,845
I thought Hiroya's words
were really wonderful.

899
00:46:55,946 --> 00:46:58,515
The idea that coming out
is not just that moment,

900
00:46:58,582 --> 00:47:02,319
but it's a lifelong process of showing
that this is what makes you happy

901
00:47:02,386 --> 00:47:04,354
and that you're genuinely happy now.

902
00:47:04,421 --> 00:47:07,391
That's what coming out is.
And I thought that was really wonderful.

903
00:47:07,457 --> 00:47:11,094
Yeah, really. And Hiroya was
patting him on the back the whole time.

904
00:47:11,161 --> 00:47:13,530
The boys are truly wonderful.

905
00:47:13,597 --> 00:47:16,266
- But the next episode is the final one!
- Argh!

906
00:47:16,333 --> 00:47:18,335
- What's going to happen?
- Is it really happening?

907
00:47:18,402 --> 00:47:20,470
- Is everything going to wrap up?
- It's gonna wrap up!

908
00:47:20,537 --> 00:47:24,208
Will everything be okay? I hope Taeheon
doesn't see what happened as a big issue.

909
00:47:24,274 --> 00:47:26,376
- Right at the very end.
- What?

910
00:47:26,443 --> 00:47:28,412
- Truly.
- I wonder what's going to happen.
